Package org.sbml.jsbml.ext.comp

Class CompSBMLDocumentPlugin

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sbml.jsbml.AbstractTreeNode
      • org.sbml.jsbml.ext.AbstractSBasePlugin
        • org.sbml.jsbml.ext.comp.CompSBasePlugin
          • org.sbml.jsbml.ext.comp.CompSBMLDocumentPlugin
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, javax.swing.tree.TreeNode, SBasePlugin, TreeNodeWithChangeSupport

    public class CompSBMLDocumentPlugin
extends CompSBasePlugin
    Allows SBML documents to contain more than one model.

    The top level of an SBMLDocument is a container whose structure is defined by the object class SBML in the SBML Level 3 Version 1 Core specification. In Level 3 Core, this container can contain only one object of class Model. The Hierarchical Model Composition package allows SBML documents to contain more than one model.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Nicolas Rodriguez
